# steer
## 1.1: direct

  *  She steered the boat toward shore.
  *  He steered the team to a championship gold in the 1995 season.
  *  She steered me to the director of public relations.
  *  Prosecutors are examining whether he steered taxpayers'dollars to
  *  build a park next to his wife's day care center.
  *  Mariners used to steer by the stars.
  *  He steered around the abandoned bike.

## 1.2: avoid

  *  He steered away from questions about the likely duration of the U.S. troop buildup.
  *  He steered clear of the priesthood because he couldn't keep the vow of celibacy.
